  "steps": [
    {
      "order": 1,
      "instruction": "Grated onion - Place the breadcrumbs in a large bowl. Using a standard box grater, grate the onion over the panko so it soaks in. Mix through."
    },
    {
      "order": 2,
      "instruction": "Meatball mixture - Add remaining Meatball ingredients and mix well with your hands until thoroughly combined."
    },
    {
      "order": 3,
      "instruction": "Roll balls - Roll 20 to 22 balls (1 1/2 tablespoons of mixture). I use an ice cream scoop with lever, handy!"
    },
    {
      "order": 4,
      "instruction": "Slurry - Mix ingredients in a bowl until smooth. We will use this to thicken the gravy (no lumpy gravy, yay!)"
    },
    {
      "order": 5,
      "instruction": "Brown meatballs - Heat the oil in a large skillet over high heat. Cook meatballs, using tablespoons to roll (to minimise deforming) until browned on the outside but still raw inside. Remove onto a plate and set aside."
    },
    {
      "order": 6,
      "instruction": "Sauté mushrooms - Melt butter in the same skillet still on high. Cook mushrooms until they start to soften (~ 2 minutes). Add salt, pepper and the garlic, then cook for a further 2 minutes until the garlic is golden and mushrooms are soft."
    },
    {
      "order": 7,
      "instruction": "Make gravy - Add beef stock, salt, pepper and slurry, then stir to combine."
    },
    {
      "order": 8,
      "instruction": "Simmer meatballs - Once the liquid starts to simmer, add meatballs and any juices pooled on the plate. Adjust heat to medium so it&#39;s simmering gently and cook for 5 minutes until gravy is thickened and meatballs are cooked through."
    },
    {
      "order": 9,
      "instruction": "Serve over mash sprinkled with parsley if desired."
    }
  ]
}